<li id="cite_note-Grover-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Grover_39-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grover_39-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grover_39-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grover_39-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Grover_39-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGrover" class="citation journal cs1">Grover, Mark. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dialoguejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/sbi/articles/Dialogue_V17N03_25.pdf">"Religious Accommodation in the Land of Racial Democracy: Mormon Priesthood and Black Brazilians"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">April 17,</span> 2023</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=Religious+Accommodation+in+the+Land+of+Racial+Democracy%3A+Mormon+Priesthood+and+Black+Brazilians&amp;rft.aulast=Grover&amp;rft.aufirst=Mark&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dialoguejournal.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsbi%2Farticles%2FDialogue_V17N03_25.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
