<li id="cite_note-Complicated-40"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Complicated_40-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHarris2018" class="citation journal cs1">Harris, Matthew L. (October 1, 2018). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dialoguejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/sbi/articles/Dialogue_V51N03_4.pdf">"Mormons and Lineage: The Complicated History of Blacks and Patriarchal Blessings, 1830–2018"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>51</b> (3). <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>: 83–130. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.51.3.0083">10.5406/dialjmormthou.51.3.0083</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:171495031">171495031</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=Mormons+and+Lineage%3A+The+Complicated+History+of+Blacks+and+Patriarchal+Blessings%2C+1830%E2%80%932018&amp;rft.volume=51&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=83-130&amp;rft.date=2018-10-01&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fdialjmormthou.51.3.0083&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A171495031%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft.aulast=Harris&amp;rft.aufirst=Matthew+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dialoguejournal.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsbi%2Farticles%2FDialogue_V51N03_4.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Balmer-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Balmer_41-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Balmer_41-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBalmerRiess2015" class="citation book cs1">Balmer, Randall; <a href="/wiki/Jana_Riess" title="Jana Riess">Riess, Jana</a> (December 8, 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=mQ7TCgAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA168"><i>Mormonism and American Politics</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Columbia_University_Press" title="Columbia University Press">Columbia University Press</a>. p.&#160;168. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780231540896" title="Special:BookSources/9780231540896"><bdi>9780231540896</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+and+American+Politics&amp;rft.pages=168&amp;rft.pub=Columbia+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2015-12-08&amp;rft.isbn=9780231540896&amp;rft.aulast=Balmer&amp;rft.aufirst=Randall&amp;rft.au=Riess%2C+Jana&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DmQ7TCgAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA168&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Image-42"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Image_42-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Image_42-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReynolds1868" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/George_Reynolds_(Mormon)" title="George Reynolds (Mormon)">Reynolds, George</a> (November 15, 1868). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/juvenileinstruct322geor/page/173/mode/1up">"Man and His Varieties: Food-Habits-Religion, Etc"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Juvenile_Instructor" title="Juvenile Instructor">Juvenile Instructor</a></i>. <b>3</b> (22): 173 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>For the day will come ... when all men will lose their extravagances of character and appearance, and become 'a white and delightsome people' physically as well as morally. When they will be as God first made Adam 'in his own image' and 'very good.'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Juvenile+Instructor&amp;rft.atitle=Man+and+His+Varieties%3A+Food-Habits-Religion%2C+Etc.&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=22&amp;rft.pages=173&amp;rft.date=1868-11-15&amp;rft.aulast=Reynolds&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fjuvenileinstruct322geor%2Fpage%2F173%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-kidd-43"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-kidd_43-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-kidd_43-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFKidd2006" class="citation book cs1">Kidd, Colin (2006). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=aNT3q1HjY_MC"><i>The Forging of Races: Race and Scripture in the Protestant Atlantic World, 1600–2000</i></a>. Cambridge, England: <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780521793247" title="Special:BookSources/9780521793247"><bdi>9780521793247</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Forging+of+Races%3A+Race+and+Scripture+in+the+Protestant+Atlantic+World%2C+1600%E2%80%932000&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+England&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=9780521793247&amp;rft.aulast=Kidd&amp;rft.aufirst=Colin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DaNT3q1HjY_MC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReynolds1868" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/George_Reynolds_(Mormon)" title="George Reynolds (Mormon)">Reynolds, George</a> (October 15, 1868). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/juvenileinstruct320geor/page/157/mode/1up">"Man and His Varieties: The Negro Race"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Juvenile_Instructor" class="mw-redirect" title="The Juvenile Instructor">The Juvenile Instructor</a></i>. <b>3</b> (20): 157 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Archive.org" class="mw-redirect" title="Archive.org">Archive.org</a>. <q>We understand that when God made man in his own image and pronounced him very good, that he made him white. We have no record of any of God's favored servants being of a black race. All His prophets and apostles belonged to the most handsome race on the face of the earth .... In this race was born His Son Jesus, who, we are told was very lovely, and 'in the express image of his Father's person, and every angel who ever brought a message of God's mercy to man was beautiful to look upon, clad in the purest white and with a countenance bright as the noonday sun.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Juvenile+Instructor&amp;rft.atitle=Man+and+His+Varieties%3A+The+Negro+Race&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=20&amp;rft.pages=157&amp;rft.date=1868-10-15&amp;rft.aulast=Reynolds&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fjuvenileinstruct320geor%2Fpage%2F157%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-45"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-45">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFClervaud2022" class="citation thesis cs1">Clervaud, Fraendy (April 2022). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://digitalcommons.liberty.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1849&amp;context=masters"><i>Debunking the Curse of Ham and its Generational Impact on the Black Race</i></a> (Thesis). <a href="/wiki/Liberty_University" title="Liberty University">Liberty University</a>. p.&#160;54. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20221207204126/https://digitalcommons.liberty.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1849&amp;context=masters">Archived</a> from the original on December 7, 2022 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adissertation&amp;rft.title=Debunking+the+Curse+of+Ham+and+its+Generational+Impact+on+the+Black+Race&amp;rft.inst=Liberty+University&amp;rft.date=2022-04&amp;rft.aulast=Clervaud&amp;rft.aufirst=Fraendy&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.liberty.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1849%26context%3Dmasters&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-46"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-46">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAndersen2020" class="citation news cs1">Andersen, Emily (July 21, 2020). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://universe.byu.edu/2020/07/21/the-color-of-christ-how-has-art-affected-racism-in-the-church/">"The color of Christ: How has art affected racism in the Church?"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Daily_Universe" class="mw-redirect" title="Daily Universe">Daily Universe</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Daily+Universe&amp;rft.atitle=The+color+of+Christ%3A+How+has+art+affected+racism+in+the+Church%3F&amp;rft.date=2020-07-21&amp;rft.aulast=Andersen&amp;rft.aufirst=Emily&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Funiverse.byu.edu%2F2020%2F07%2F21%2Fthe-color-of-christ-how-has-art-affected-racism-in-the-church%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
