<li id="cite_note-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFvan_Frank2010" class="citation web cs1">van Frank, Megan (November 5, 2010). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.utahhumanities.org/stories/items/show/201">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>'Slavery of African-Americans in Early Utah,' Utah Stories from the Beehive Archive"</a>. <i>utahhumanities.org</i>. Utah Humanities<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">April 17,</span> 2023</span>. <q>Brigham Young declared slaveholding to be a practice ordained by God, but was not in favor of creating a slave-based economy in Utah</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=utahhumanities.org&amp;rft.atitle=%27Slavery+of+African-Americans+in+Early+Utah%2C%27+Utah+Stories+from+the+Beehive+Archive&amp;rft.date=2010-11-05&amp;rft.aulast=van+Frank&amp;rft.aufirst=Megan&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.utahhumanities.org%2Fstories%2Fitems%2Fshow%2F201&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
