<li id="cite_note-Repugnant-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Repugnant_75-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooks2020" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joanna_Brooks" title="Joanna Brooks">Brooks, Joanna</a> (May 2020). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=IcDgDwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA123"><i>Mormonism and White Supremacy: American Religion and The Problem of Racial Innocence</i></a>. New York City: <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. pp.&#160;121–123. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780190081751" title="Special:BookSources/9780190081751"><bdi>9780190081751</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>Furthermore, your ideas, as we understand them, appear to contemplate the intermarriage of the Negro and the White races, a concept which has heretofore been most repugnant to most normal-minded people from the ancient patriarchs till now. ... We are not unmindful of the fact that there is a growing tendency ... toward the breaking down of race barriers in the matter of intermarriage between whites and blacks, but it does not have the sanction of the Church and is contrary to Church doctrine.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormonism+and+White+Supremacy%3A+American+Religion+and+The+Problem+of+Racial+Innocence&amp;rft.place=New+York+City&amp;rft.pages=121-123&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2020-05&amp;rft.isbn=9780190081751&amp;rft.aulast=Brooks&amp;rft.aufirst=Joanna&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DIcDgDwAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA123&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Virus-76"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Virus_76-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFClark1946" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/J._Reuben_Clark" title="J. Reuben Clark">Clark, J. Reuben</a> (August 1946). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/stream/improvementera4908unse#page/n13/mode/2up">"Plain Talk to Girls"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Improvement_Era" title="Improvement Era">Improvement Era</a></i>. <b>49</b> (8): 492<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">April 17,</span> 2023</span> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>It is sought today in certain quarters to break down all race prejudice, and at the end of the road ... is intermarriage. ...[D]o not ever let that wicked virus get into your systems that brotherhood either permits or entitles you to mix races which are inconsistent. Biologically, it is wrong; spiritually, it is wrong.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Improvement+Era&amp;rft.atitle=Plain+Talk+to+Girls&amp;rft.volume=49&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.pages=492&amp;rft.date=1946-08&amp;rft.aulast=Clark&amp;rft.aufirst=J.+Reuben&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Fimprovementera4908unse%23page%2Fn13%2Fmode%2F2up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-77"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-77">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMargaret_Blair_Young,_Darius_Aidan_Gray2013" class="citation book cs1">Margaret Blair Young, Darius Aidan Gray (August 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=rKGCAwAAQBAJ"><i>The Last Mile of the Way: Standing on the Promises,Book 3</i></a>. Provo, Utah: Zarahemla Books. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780988323308" title="Special:BookSources/9780988323308"><bdi>9780988323308</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Last+Mile+of+the+Way%3A+Standing+on+the+Promises%2CBook+3&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Zarahemla+Books&amp;rft.date=2013-08&amp;rft.isbn=9780988323308&amp;rft.au=Margaret+Blair+Young%2C+Darius+Aidan+Gray&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DrKGCAwAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
