<li id="cite_note-Prince-79"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Prince_79-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPrince2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gregory_Prince" title="Gregory Prince">Prince, Gregory A.</a> (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=3UBXLIkLEQwC"><i>David O. McKay and the Rise of Modern Mormonism</i></a>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/University_of_Utah_Press" title="University of Utah Press">University of Utah Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87480-822-7" title="Special:BookSources/0-87480-822-7"><bdi>0-87480-822-7</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=David+O.+McKay+and+the+Rise+of+Modern+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Utah+Press&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=0-87480-822-7&amp;rft.aulast=Prince&amp;rft.aufirst=Gregory+A.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D3UBXLIkLEQwC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
