<li id="cite_note-103"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-103">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation journal cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/stream/improvementera7302unse#page/n71/mode/1up">"Letter of First Presidency Clarifies Church's Position on the Negro"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Improvement_Era" title="Improvement Era">Improvement Era</a></i>. <b>73</b> (2): 70–71. February 1970<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">April 17,</span> 2023</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Improvement+Era&amp;rft.atitle=Letter+of+First+Presidency+Clarifies+Church%27s+Position+on+the+Negro&amp;rft.volume=73&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=70-71&amp;rft.date=1970-02&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fstream%2Fimprovementera7302unse%23page%2Fn71%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
