<li id="cite_note-104"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-104">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLeBaron2016" class="citation book cs1">LeBaron, E. Dale (October 6, 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=BBzmDAAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA82">"Mormonism in black Africa"</a>. In Davies, Douglas J. (ed.). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=BBzmDAAAQBAJ"><i>Mormon Identities in Transition</i></a> (2016&#160;ed.). London: <a href="/wiki/Bloomsbury_Publishing" title="Bloomsbury Publishing">Bloomsbury Publishing</a>. p.&#160;82. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781474281294" title="Special:BookSources/9781474281294"><bdi>9781474281294</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Mormonism+in+black+Africa&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Identities+in+Transition&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=82&amp;rft.edition=2016&amp;rft.pub=Bloomsbury+Publishing&amp;rft.date=2016-10-06&amp;rft.isbn=9781474281294&amp;rft.aulast=LeBaron&amp;rft.aufirst=E.+Dale&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBBzmDAAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA82&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-105"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-105">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.newspapers.com/clip/21138508/partial-transcript-of-ap-interview-with/">"New policy occasions church comment"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Times-News_(Burlington,_North_Carolina)" title="Times-News (Burlington, North Carolina)">Times-News</a></i>. Burlington, North Carolina. <a href="/wiki/Associated_Press" title="Associated Press">Associated Press</a>. June 9, 1988 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Newspapers.com" class="mw-redirect" title="Newspapers.com">Newspapers.com</a>. <q>AP: Was the ban on ordaining [Black people] to the priesthood a matter of policy or doctrine? ... OAKS: I don't know that its possible to distinguish between policy and doctrine in a church that believes in continuing revelation and sustains its leader as a prophet. ... I'm not sure I could justify the difference in doctrine and policy in the fact that before 1978 a person could not hold the priesthood and after 1978 they could hold the priesthood. AP: Did you feel differently about the issue before the revelation was given? OAKS: I decided a long time ago, 1961 or 2, that there's no way to talk about it in terms of doctrine, or policy, practice, procedure. All of those words just lead you to reaffirm your prejudice, whichever it was.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Times-News&amp;rft.atitle=New+policy+occasions+church+comment&amp;rft.date=1988-06-09&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newspapers.com%2Fclip%2F21138508%2Fpartial-transcript-of-ap-interview-with%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-106"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-106">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFEdmunds2013" class="citation news cs1">Edmunds, Tressa (March 5, 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2013/mar/05/mormons-black-priests-ban">"Mormons can finally say 'we got it wrong' over black priest ban"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i>. <q>It wasn't until 1978 that black men were again allowed to receive the priesthood and black women were allowed to attend the temple. Most members were unaware that there was ever a time when black people were allowed equal participation in the gospel. ... In 1978 the prophet Spencer W Kimball announced the lifting of the priesthood ban and temple restriction....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=Mormons+can+finally+say+%27we+got+it+wrong%27+over+black+priest+ban&amp;rft.date=2013-03-05&amp;rft.aulast=Edmunds&amp;rft.aufirst=Tressa&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2Fbelief%2F2013%2Fmar%2F05%2Fmormons-black-priests-ban&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-107"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-107">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGrover1990" class="citation journal cs1">Grover, Mark L. (Spring 1990). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dialoguejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/sbi/articles/Dialogue_V23N01_41.pdf">"The Mormon Priesthood Revelation and the São Paulo Brazil Temple"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>23</b> (1). <a href="/wiki/University_of_Illinois_Press" title="University of Illinois Press">University of Illinois Press</a>: 39–53. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F45225842">10.2307/45225842</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/45225842">45225842</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:254321222">254321222</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=The+Mormon+Priesthood+Revelation+and+the+S%C3%A3o+Paulo+Brazil+Temple&amp;rft.ssn=spring&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=39-53&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A254321222%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F45225842%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F45225842&amp;rft.aulast=Grover&amp;rft.aufirst=Mark+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dialoguejournal.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsbi%2Farticles%2FDialogue_V23N01_41.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
