<li id="cite_note-117"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-117">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFRiess2019" class="citation news cs1"><a href="/wiki/Jana_Riess" title="Jana Riess">Riess, Jana</a> (July 19, 2019). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://religionnews.com/2019/07/19/will-the-mormon-president-apologize-to-the-naacp-for-the-churchs-past-racism/">"Will the Mormon president apologize to the NAACP for the church's past racism?"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Religion_News_Service" title="Religion News Service">Religion News Service</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Will+the+Mormon+president+apologize+to+the+NAACP+for+the+church%27s+past+racism%3F&amp;rft.date=2019-07-19&amp;rft.aulast=Riess&amp;rft.aufirst=Jana&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Freligionnews.com%2F2019%2F07%2F19%2Fwill-the-mormon-president-apologize-to-the-naacp-for-the-churchs-past-racism%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
