<li id="cite_note-160"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-160">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReeve2019" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/W._Paul_Reeve" title="W. Paul Reeve">Reeve, W. Paul</a> (August 23, 2019). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://crdh.rrchnm.org/essays/v02-03-century-of-black-mormons/">"Century of Black Mormons A Preliminary Interpretation of the Data"</a>. <i>Current Research in Digital History</i>. <b>2</b>. <a href="/wiki/George_Mason_University" title="George Mason University">George Mason University</a>. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.31835%2Fcrdh.2019.03">10.31835/crdh.2019.03</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:202353551">202353551</a>. <q>Dr. Jacob Rugh at Brigham Young University estimates that in 2018 there were one million black Latter-day Saints globally.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Current+Research+in+Digital+History&amp;rft.atitle=Century+of+Black+Mormons+A+Preliminary+Interpretation+of+the+Data&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.date=2019-08-23&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.31835%2Fcrdh.2019.03&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A202353551%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft.aulast=Reeve&amp;rft.aufirst=W.+Paul&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fcrdh.rrchnm.org%2Fessays%2Fv02-03-century-of-black-mormons%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Grappling-161"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Grappling_161-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-mormon-church-black-members-20180601-story.html">"Mormons grappling with race issues 40 years after church's ban on Black leaders was lifted"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Los_Angeles_Times" title="Los Angeles Times">Los Angeles Times</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Associated_Press" title="Associated Press">Associated Press</a>. June 1, 2018. <q>The number of black Mormons has grown, but still only accounts for an estimated 6% of 16 million [or 960,000] worldwide members. Not one serves in the highest levels of global leadership.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Los+Angeles+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Mormons+grappling+with+race+issues+40+years+after+church%27s+ban+on+Black+leaders+was+lifted&amp;rft.date=2018-06-01&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fnation%2Fla-na-mormon-church-black-members-20180601-story.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABlack+people+and+Mormonism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
